==English==
{{wikipedia|Quantity}}

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|amounten|lang=enm||to mount up to, come up to, signify}}, from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|amounter|lang=fro||to amount to}}, from {{term|amunt|lang=fro}}, {{term|amont|lang=fro||uphill, upward}}, prop. prep. phr. {{term|a mont|lang=fro||toward or to a mountain or heap}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|ad montem|lang=la}}, from {{term|ad|lang=la||to}} + {{term|montem|lang=la}}, accusative of {{term|mons|lang=la||mountain}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|ə.mount'}}, {{IPA|/əˈmaʊnt/}}, {{X-SAMPA|/@"maUnt/}}
* {{audio|en-us-amount.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|aʊnt}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The [[total]], [[aggregate]] or [[sum]] of material.  Not applicable to discrete numbers or units or items.
# A [[quantity]] or [[volume]].
#: ''Pour a small '''amount''' of water into the dish.''
#: ''The dogs need different '''amounts''' of food.''
